OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F393A1747816480
OL,3,CWords of heartbroken mother read out
OL,4,Cin Parliament in emotional speech by MP
OL,6,F"To lose a child to murder in your own
OL,7,Fhome while trying to protect them is a
OL,8,Fburden no parent should ever be asked
OL,9,Fto bear. But under our current justice
OL,10,Fsystem, convicted criminals can opt-
OL,11,Fout of attending their own sentencing.
OL,13,F"That's what Olivia's murderer did.
OL,14,FCashman remained in his cell, refusing
OL,15,Fto face the court, to hear Cheryl's
OL,16,Fwords, to look her in the eye. It was
OL,17,Fthe act of a coward. That injustice
OL,18,Fmust end.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
