OL,3,CWords of heartbroken mother read out
OL,4,Cin Parliament in emotional speech by MP
OL,6,F"Let her words ring out in this
OL,7,Fchamber, like they should have done in
OL,8,FCashman's ears that day."
OL,10,FIn her victim statement, Ms Korbel
OL,11,Fdescribed Olivia as "the light of our
OL,12,Flives, our beautiful, sassy, chatty
OL,13,Fgirl who never ran out of energy".
OL,15,FMs Korbel had also said: "My worst
OL,16,Fnightmare was being separated from Liv
OL,17,Fand not being with her when she needed
OL,18,Fme the most, I was the first person to
OL,19,Fhold my baby girl, and as her mum, I
OL,20,Fshould have been the last.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@YO]sD@UOUuD@aO]wD@ZOU
